  "body": "Erigon version: `2.28.1`\r\n\r\nWhile tracing BSC blocks with `trace_block`, the `value` field for the reward returns `0x1bc16d674ec80000` — equivalent to 2 ETH. This comes from pre-merge ETH where the miner reward per block was 2 ETH.\r\n\r\nFor ETH, this has been fixed and returns `0x0`. Can we do the same for BSC?\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n### BSC\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"method\": \"trace_block\",\r\n  \"params\": [\r\n    \"0x15c99d7\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"id\": 1,\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n👇🏻\r\n```\r\n{\r\n      \"action\": {\r\n        \"author\": \"0xa6f79b60359f141df90a0c745125b131caaffd12\",\r\n        \"rewardType\": \"block\",\r\n        \"value\": \"0x1bc16d674ec80000\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"blockHash\": \"0x967bd9a6b4d03c7886e0c8dbe49a16c1eb52efc7c7a06b52882b573c1b4629cb\",\r\n      \"blockNumber\": 22845911,\r\n      \"result\": null,\r\n      \"subtraces\": 0,\r\n      \"traceAddress\": [],\r\n      \"type\": \"reward\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### ETH\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"method\": \"trace_block\",\r\n  \"params\": [\r\n    \"0xf2e008\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"id\": 1,\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n👇🏻\r\n```\r\n{\r\n      \"action\": {\r\n        \"author\": \"0xdafea492d9c6733ae3d56b7ed1adb60692c98bc5\",\r\n        \"rewardType\": \"block\",\r\n        \"value\": \"0x0\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"blockHash\": \"0x34162a641846868ae505d3112b37ff5cf414be96f84c5fac0673972f73a09f55\",\r\n      \"blockNumber\": 15917064,\r\n      \"result\": null,\r\n      \"subtraces\": 0,\r\n      \"traceAddress\": [],\r\n      \"type\": \"reward\"\r\n}\r\n```",
