    "body": "> When is BSC suppose to have a value reward of 0?\r\n\r\nNo, BSC is not supposed to have a block reward of 0. However, while tracing a block, the current arbitrary value `0x1bc16d674ec80000` comes from the old ETH (PoW) setup. The Erigon team has already changed it to `0x0` for ETH after The Merge (PoS) (many issues for the same). Then why not do it for BSC too?\r\n\r\nDo you think `0x1bc16d674ec80000` is accurate and should stay?",
